  <span id="freeText15977349309492709059" style="display:none">When i watched the video above, i expected the book to be a powerful one, not in the sense of writing, but in the strength of the main characters. I expected a lion, righteous and proud, ready to protect the defenceless, what i got instead was a fox, scheming and cunning, ready to take down everyone, including the woman he loves. I expected a king and got a minister instead. But the minister isn’t a shoddy one, he’s the kind that keeps you occupied so much that you wouldn’t want to put down the book under any circumstances. Not even to answer nature’s call. <br />The full review is on my blog. <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://mychocolethandbag.wordpress.com/2011/08/07/chanakyas-chant-a-review-2/">http://mychocolethandbag.wordpress.co...</a></span>
