        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1156535066" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7344734155770558821">This book was a replacement by my brother for &quot;Thousand Splendid Suns&quot; as he lost it. The former book is one of my favorites. I can&apos;t say I liked Chanakya chant as much as &apos;TSS&apos;, but both are divergent from each other so who was I to judge? <br/> I started reading this one just because it was quite interesting from the excerpt. First of all, you don&apos;t have to like a story to like a book and that is something I understood after reading this one. Gangasagar was like Chanakya&apos;s in many ways but not in a</span>
  <span id="freeText7344734155770558821" style="display:none">This book was a replacement by my brother for "Thousand Splendid Suns" as he lost it. The former book is one of my favorites. I can't say I liked Chanakya chant as much as 'TSS', but both are divergent from each other so who was I to judge? <br /> I started reading this one just because it was quite interesting from the excerpt. First of all, you don't have to like a story to like a book and that is something I understood after reading this one. Gangasagar was like Chanakya's in many ways but not in all and so was the case with the story. The story is gripping, entertaining and different.I won't lie so yeah there were times when I wanted to beat the crap out of some characters but I still couldn't stop reading it. I couldn't help it. <br /><br /><br />It was also my first thriller book by an Indian author, YES YOU GUESSED RIGHT! I READ THIS BOOK A LONG TIME AGO AND I LOVED IT.I had tried reading stories (genre- romance) before by some Indian authors but i couldn't complete them.They were just so dull and uninteresting. Then, I bought Krishna Key and so came other Indian authors in my life. Right now, I am completing Amish's other series.I love his books!The Shiva Series rocks!<br /><br />But this book will always have a special place in my life!<br /><br />Five stars!<br /></span>
