<span id="freeTextContainer17697033207576219198">As every election unfolds, media and so-called sephologists go to a tizzy over someone whom they call The Chanakya. Then, as the dust settles over the landscape, either the supposed kingmaker is hailed, or the poor sod gets roasted as a con job.<br/>But what about the real deal?<br/>What if a modern incarnation of Chanakya, working with the sole aim of uniting the nation under one ruler, decides to enter the game?<br/>This novel is a case study with respect to that scenario.<br/>It&apos;s also the finest make-believe bi</span>
  <span id="freeText17697033207576219198" style="display:none">As every election unfolds, media and so-called sephologists go to a tizzy over someone whom they call The Chanakya. Then, as the dust settles over the landscape, either the supposed kingmaker is hailed, or the poor sod gets roasted as a con job.<br />But what about the real deal?<br />What if a modern incarnation of Chanakya, working with the sole aim of uniting the nation under one ruler, decides to enter the game?<br />This novel is a case study with respect to that scenario.<br />It's also the finest make-believe biographical fiction about Chanakya, that we have had.<br />Above all, it's a gripping political thriller that takes us on an utterly amoral, yet hugely entertaining ride.<br />Recommended, but please, don't try to put ALL those maxims into usage.<br />Like potent medicine, those lessons are to be taken one at a time.</span>
